    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Paintings or prints that depict beautiful women. This term, which literally means "pictures of beautiful women," was most likely coined in the Edo period (1615-1868) or the Meiji period (1868-1912). Before this period, these pictures may have been called "onna-e" or "bijin-e".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047828/JAANUS [online] (2001-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000049930/Mason, History of Japanese Art (1993)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gemälde oder Druck mit der Darstellungen von weiblichen Schönheiten. Der Begriff, der wörtlich "Bilder von schönen Frauen" bedeutet, wurde mit hoher Wahscheinlichkeit in der Edo-Periode (1615-1868) oder der Meiji-Perode (1868-1912) geprägt. Vor dieser Zeit können diese Bilder "onna-e" oder "bijin-e" geheißen haben.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>描繪美麗女子的繪畫或版畫，此詞彙字面意思為「美女圖畫」，很可能在江戶時代（西元1615至1868年）或明治時代（西元1868至1912年）才出現，在此之前，這類圖像可能稱為「女繪」或「美人繪」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Schilderijen of afdrukken met een afbeelding van een mooie vrouw. De term betekent ook letterlijk ���afbeeldingen van mooie vrouwen' en is waarschijnlijk ontstaan in de Edo-periode (1615-1868) of de Meiji-periode (1868-1912). Vóór deze periodes noemde men dit soort afbeeldingen ���onna-e' of ���bijin-e'.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
